# Scaffold CRUD Resource

Generate a complete CRUD resource across all architectural layers.

## Generated Files

### Core Layer
- `core/entities/{resource}.py` — Domain entity with value objects
- `core/interfaces/{resource}_repository.py` — Repository interface

### Application Layer
- `application/services/{resource}_service.py` — Business logic
- `application/dtos/{resource}_dto.py` — Data transfer objects
- `application/commands/{resource}_commands.py` — Create/Update/Delete commands

### Infrastructure Layer
- `infrastructure/persistence/models/{resource}_model.py` — SQLAlchemy ORM model
- `infrastructure/persistence/repositories/{resource}_repository.py` — Repository implementation

### Presentation Layer
- `presentation/api/routes/{resource}_routes.py` — FastAPI router (CRUD endpoints)
- `presentation/api/schemas/{resource}_schemas.py` — Pydantic request/response schemas

### Tests
- `tests/unit/application/test_{resource}_service.py` — Service unit tests
- `tests/integration/test_{resource}_api.py` — API integration tests
- `tests/factories/{resource}_factory.py` — Factory Boy factory

## Conventions

- Entity ID uses UUID
- All timestamps use UTC
- Soft deletes (deleted_at column) unless specified otherwise
- Pagination for list endpoints (offset/limit)
- Use keyword-only arguments everywhere
- Full type annotations on all functions

## Verification

```bash
task lint && task typecheck && task test:unit
```
